Colour pattern .
Background opaque greysh-white; carapace with two very broad, transverse, brown or greybrown bands; each abdominal somite with a broad transverse, brown or dark grey-brown band; post-rostral plate dark brown-grey on margins; antennular and antennal flagella orange-yellow; chelipeds with ischium, merus and carpus marbled with brown; mesial face of major chela marbled with brown and whitish and with numerous interconnecting white spots, pale yellowish area usually present on proximal half; dactylus and pollex brown and whitespotted except for hyaline-pink distal areas; mesial face of minor chela brown with some white marbling and spotting; second to fifth pereiopods yellow; telson and uropods mostly brown or dark-grey, with some white or paleorange areas ( Figs. 12 , 13 ); younger individuals with larger white band across proximal portion of major chela palm ( Fig. 13A, B ), this band being later replaced by a pale beige patch ( Fig. 13C, D ). See also colour descriptions in Rankin (1900) , Verrill (1922 , as
A. armillatus
) and Boone (1930 , as
